<font color="#FF0000">REAL TRUST</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov 17 16:08:51 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Anne<br>
Talk about trust, when I was in Nam, I had asked my then wife, to go to the neighborhood Army Surplus store and buy me a rain suit. I trusted her, she send me a bright yellow florescence rain suit the kind that highway workers use so that on coming traffic can see them. If I had worn it, every Charlie for miles around would have seen me coming. <br><br>
MTF would have had to put on his sissy, sunglasses just to talk to me and he would have been able to read his big bird watch in the dark by just standing next to me. Yep, I trusted her. <br><br>
If I did not write her she would call the Red Cross,  just in case I was no longer there. Learned a lot about her, after I came home. I better stop here, that’s altogether another story.<br>

